column2: (n.) A carnivorous quadruped, (Proteles Lalandii), of South Africa, resembling the fox and hyena. See Proteles.
(a.) Pertaining to Aaron, the first high priest of the Jews.
(n.) A worshiper of Baal; a devotee of any false religion; an idolater.
(v. i.) To unite in a small party to promote private views and interests by intrigue; to intrigue; to plot.
(n.) One who dips slightly into anything; a superficial meddler.
(n.) The state or quality of being eager; ardent desire.
(a.) Belonging to a faction; being a partisan; taking sides.
(v. t.) Place where anything is commonly found.
(n.) The act of inhabiting; state of inhabiting or dwelling, or of being inhabited; occupancy.
(n.) Place of abode; settled dwelling; residence; house.
(n.) A foot consisting of a short syllable followed by a long one, as in /mans, or of an unaccented syllable followed by an accented one, as invent; an iambic. See the Couplet under Iambic, n.
(a.) Of or pertaining to Japan, or to the lacquered work of that country; as, Japan ware.
